    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-09-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="201"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Planten</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1894</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Replying to yours of the 31st ultimo, I have the
                    honor to inform you that the Secretary of the Treasury has been notified as to
                    your request, that the colonies of Curaçao, Buen Ayre, Oruba, St. Martin, St.
                    Eustatius, and Saba do not impose duties on salt, those duties having been
                    abolished six years ago.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
